items.title: Australian Woman, Erin Patterson, Gets Life in Mushroom Murder Case
items.description: Erin Patterson was found guilty of murdering three of her husband’s relatives and trying to kill a fourth by serving them deadly mushrooms.

items.title: Millions of Londoners Brace for Transit Disruption as Tube Strike Begins
items.description: A strike on the London Underground began Sunday over pay and conditions, threatening to upend commuter journeys for most of the week.

items.title: A View From Inside Iran
items.description: Our correspondent found a sense of apprehension in the country after the 12-day war with Israel.

items.title: Brazilians Protest as Bolsonaro Coup Trial Nears Verdict
items.description: Tensions are heating up in Brazil as the nation enters the final week of former President Jair Bolsonaro’s trial on attempted coup charges.
